    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The randomization services provided in GameplayKit are suitable for reliably creating deterministic, pseudorandom gameplay mechanics, but are not cryptographically robust. For cryptography, obfuscation, or cipher uses, use the Security framework, described in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Cryptographic Services Guide",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Security/Conceptual/cryptoservices/Introduction/Introduction.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40011172"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To generate basic random values with this random source, use the methods defined in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrandom"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " protocol. To generate random values with a specific range and distribution, use this random source with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrandomdistribution"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class or one of its subclasses."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you create an instance of this class, the resulting random source is both "
            },
            {
              "type": "newTerm",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "independent"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "newTerm",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "deterministic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "â€”that is, the sequence of numbers generated by one instance has no effect on the sequence generated by any other instance, and that sequence can be replicated when necessary. For details on replicating sequences, see the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gklinearcongruentialrandomsource/1501103-seed"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gklinearcongruentialrandomsource/1501164-initwithseed"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " initializer."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The linear congruential random source uses the algorithm described by Donald E. Knuth in "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The Art of Computer Programming"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", Volume 2: "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Seminumerical Algorithms"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", section 3.2.1, with the common seed mask value of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0x5DEECE66D"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". This random source is therefore compatible with other implementations of that algorithm, including the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "java.util.Random"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class in Java. That is, if you initialize a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gklinearcongruentialrandomsource"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance and a compatible implementation using the same seed value, both generate the same sequence of numbers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information on choosing and using randomizers in GameplayKit, read "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Randomization",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/RandomSources.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172-CH9"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "GameplayKit Programming Guide",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
